Constant Field Values

TCL_PROCEDURE

private static final String TCL_PROCEDURE
Called TCL procedure within the TCL update to parse the new policy definition. The TCL procedure calls method jpoCallExecute(ParameterCache_mxJPO, String...) with the new policy definition. All quot's are replaced by @0@0@ and all apostroph's are replaced by @1@1@.

See Also:

_preTCLCode - TCL code which is defined before the source file is sourced

_sourceFile - souce file with the TCL code to update

jpoCallExecute

public void jpoCallExecute(ParameterCache_mxJPO _paramCache,
                           String... _args)
                    throws Exception
The method is called within the update of an administration object. The method is called directly within the update.
  • All @0@0@ are replaced by quot's and all @1@1@ are replaced by apostroph's.
  • The new policy definition is parsed.
  • A delta MQL script generated to update the policy to the new target definition.
  • All symbolic names for states are defined (as property on the policy).
  • The delta MQL script is executed.

Overrides:
jpoCallExecute in class AbstractPropertyObject_mxJPO
Parameters:
_paramCache - parameter cache
_args - arguments from the TCL procedure
Throws:
Exception - if a state is not defined anymore or the policy could not be updated
